I went for lunch with a couple of coworkers and it was pretty disappointing. Service was slow - there was only one woman actually doing her best to cover both the bar and dining room, but there seemed to be two managers who did little else other than talk to customers.  For a steakhouse, it was silly that there was no steak option on the lunch menu. There were sandwiches and burgers and salads, and a bunch of appetizers that promised more than what the entrées delivered.  I had a burger with a side salad and the only unique thing about it was that there were olives in the salad. The burger was clearly from a frozen puck and although it was cooked to my order, it was nothing near justifying the price.  The menu needs some clarification and improvements, and definitely a steak option for lunch. There should have been another person serving either the bar or the dining room.  Also, it's difficult to be a professional and maintain your dignity when you have to use the same parking lot as a strip club that is right next door, blasting music onto their smoking patio a few feet away from the Grill entrance.  For the price and quality presently offered, I won't go back. Since they clearly won't be able change their next door neighbor, I definitely won't be back.

When you require customers to pay 20% tip no matter what - that usually means your service and  food are damn near impeccable. At least that's what I find in NYC where I live and dine frequently.Not true in my one and only experience at this restaurant. I will not be back. The only reason this rating is 2 stars instead of one is due to the dessert. Really. And I don't think the restaurant makes it.  Let's start with having a 7:30pm reservation, being seated on time - and not seeing ANY food at our table until 8:40pm, not even bread. We knew something was up when people around us who were seated later than us, had their entrée before we had bread. When we questioned the waitress, she cited that the kitchen was backed up and that the size of our party (5) might have something to do with it. Umm - there was a party of 5 nearby us, seated after us noshing on their steaks. No pass!  Food: My rib eye steak tasted bland (no seasonings). I requested Medium (warm) and it came partially medium rare and partially well done. How do you do that? I asked the waitress for steak sauce, but by the time she got back with it, I was done trying to deal with the bland beast.  My mother's Chilean sea bass was such a disappointment she didn't finish it - citing it smelled fishy and was probably spoiled (FYI fresh Chileans sea bass does NOT smell fishy. If fresh and cooked properly, it tastes like a cross between buttery lobster and fish.)  Mom said the rice it came with was a minute rice (my mother is from the South - she knows good rice) and the topping was too sweet. She had been at this restaurant 3 times before a year ago and found this dish to be her favorite. So to come back to find the quality went totally downhill was a disappointment.  She sent it back, telling the waitress why, A few minutes later, the waitress came back with an explanation from the kitchen - citing the source for their Chilean sea bass had changed since my mother last came to the restaurant. They would be returning to their previous source in a few months and encouraged Mom to come back. (Which she will not be)  I will say my 93 year old grandmother put a world of hurt on her swordfish plate - so I guess that dish was ok. My dad silently finished his filet mignon, but he was hungry after waiting so long (our entrees didn't come until almost 9pm) My aunt wrestled with her sous vide 1/2 chicken served with bacon-shallot roasted potatoes and vegetable. She doggy bagged most of it because  "there was no bacon in that!" ...but seriously, she didn't like her food.  It got better in the end. We ordered the Lady Finger cheesecake - SO so good. The cheesecake is like a mousse - light and creamy. The waitress, surprised my dad with a slice of free cheesecake for his birthday after she overheard us talking about it. Which he appreciated and promptly ate...leaving only a sliver of graham cracker crust as its memorial  The rest of use split the Kentucky Bourbon butter cake. It sounded better than it tasted - but it was ok.  The waitress also did her best to rectify our situation by not charging us for the Chilean sea bass or the cocktail my aunt ordered and disliked. But really - when you REQUIRE patrons to pay 20% tip, the food and service need to be on-point. Not perfect, but on-point. The waitress did apologize profusely, including "ma'am-ing" us to death. Not sure whether she was new, just having an off-night or no one has ever taken her to task for service.  And please note: I have been a waitress before, so I am all about tipping properly - in exchange for good service. I am fine paying premium prices - if the food is off-the-chain, which this was not. And I also really get that no one and nothing is perfect. But if you are going to REQUIRE people to pay 20%, you better be damn near it, most of the time - on fleek!

My friends and I probably have visited the 350 Grill from the time it opened until not too long ago - most definitely for the last time. I'd like to warn all future (and current) customers of the unfortunate changes the business owners decided to put into place.   I went to dinner with 2 of my friends, of which 1 was to arrive about 45 minutes after our arrival. Our 3rd friend messaged us to order the entree so it would be about ready by the time they arrive. Right after we received the message and placed the order our friend messaged again to let us know that they would be delayed. Immediately (approx. 2 min after having placed the order with the waiter) we called the waiter back to the table and asked to delay all of our orders for a few minutes. The initial response was "We can't do that." At my question why that was the case I received the answer "I put the order in the computer, we can't stop the order now." He was kind enough to "make an exception" and came back a few minutes later to tell us that the cook decided not to start cooking yet. Just about 20 min later we found out that unfortunately our 3rd party wasn't going to make it at all. We asked the waiter to cancel one of the placed entrees and go ahead to cook our two entrees. The waiter said "I can't cancel the 3rd one, you HAVE to order it." I explained that we would not need it, the waiter immediately said "do you want to speak to the manager about this?" The manager who came to the table was a snotty, rude and arrogant 20+ year old kid who explained to us that once an order has been placed it cannot be cancelled. I asked if the entree had been cooked already and he said "no", but that it still could not be cancelled. I explained once again that only the two of us would eat, and his response was "the third order has to be cooked, if you don't want to eat it that's your choice." When I responded with "So if i don't eat it, I certainly wouldn't have to pay for it, right?" he said "Of course you have to pay for it, whether you eat it or not. You ordered it, and we will cook it and you will pay for it. It's your choice to eat it or not." Outrageous! We ended up asking for all three entrees to go, and seriously were asked when paying for it if we needed change or if the rest would be a tip. Absolutely horrific experience all in all. This place has been going down over the years. First they eliminated modifications to their meals (forget to remove blue cheese from a steak even though you may be deadly allergic to it.. guess you have to eat something else). Then they added cork fee to the menu (yes, you buy a bottle of wine and they add $20 --- TWENTY dollars to the bottle price for walking to your table with the bottle and to open it for you), recently they decided to (I guess depending on how business is going that particular night) force a gratuity on ANY size party of $20 or more. I frequently dine out and have recommended this place to colleagues and friends. Needless to say I will do the opposite from now on. Avoid this place at all costs... I can assure you it won't last no longer than another year with these rules in place (unless they can pawn off burger and fries to the visitors of the next door strip club). Too bad a negative rating isn't possible here..................
